Title: Outlook Weekend: Literary SOS
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswt5w
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 10 Jun 2018
When Sally Bayley was 14, she hit rock bottom. She was in care, had been rejected by her family and she wasn't eating. So who did she turn to when she was at her lowest? Shakespeare. Through reading, she was taken to places she could have never imagined. Image: open book on the beach Credit: Eskemar/iStock /Getty Images Plus Presenter: Emily Webb Show less